ro-establishment district councillors with solid district work. The pro-establishment camp held on to just 59 seats &ndash; a record low, thus ceding control of the district council seats on the Election Committee to the pan-dems in the next election, due in 2022.<br />\n<br />\nA relative calm returned in the days preceding polling on November 24. But rallies on all manner of causes, including thanking the US for passing legislation to impose sanctions on Hong Kong, immediately followed.<br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"color: red;\">Emboldened by the electoral success of anti-government candidates, including many who had stood with the rioters, the successful holding of the district council elections &ndash; viewed by a self-congratulatory government as an achievement &ndash; will not bring peace.</span></strong><br />\n<br />\n<strong><span style=\"color: red;\">Rather, the rioters, and their behind-the-scenes backers, will become more aggressive in pressing their demands. Their supporters may soon have to live with the consequences of legitimising street violence and discrimination against compatriots of mainland Chinese origin.</span></strong><br />\n<br />\nsource: <a href=\"https://www.scmp.com/comment/opinion/article/3039891/anti-government-victory-hong-kongs-district-council-elections-wont\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scmp.com%2Fcomment%2Fopinion%2Farticle%2F3039891%2Fanti-government-victory-hong-kongs-district-council-elections-wont&d=HsMqQMGMM0KOGi%2FJd%2BN0B8TiFwqRwBg1VWT7Je45URE%3D&h=94bbd9df\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.scmp.com/comment/opinion/article/3039891/anti-government-victory-hong-kongs-district-council-elections-wont</a>"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-12-01T05:29:35.000Z","msg":"五大訴求入面無包括贏區選<br />\n咁梗係唔會和平啦, 佢都傻既"},{"pid":"839f1e3e9f0d7901156e4a29ed2f4b16ad515b6d","tid":1764282,"uid":137569,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"b94c44aa0112fd73ab6cfbeebd53c295cdbb2328","tid":17642